1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,332
Bibrivale Lipogam at Brivail.

2
00:00:02,332 --> 00:00:07,722
Retail activity on SpaceX is abnormal, and it's just the beginning.

3
00:00:07,722 --> 00:00:15,685
Around me, people who have never bought a stock in their life are looking to put money into SpaceX.

4
00:00:15,685 --> 00:00:18,822
People who don't play the stock market.

5
00:00:18,822 --> 00:00:21,799
Who have no theory about the markets.

6
00:00:21,799 --> 00:00:24,373
And suddenly they want to share.

7
00:00:24,373 --> 00:00:26,866
This should tell you something.

8
00:00:26,866 --> 00:00:29,923
Because this is non investor behavior.

9
00:00:29,923 --> 00:00:31,773
It's believer behavior.

10
00:00:31,773 --> 00:00:35,313
And this is exactly where everyone is wrong.

11
00:00:35,313 --> 00:00:41,185
They are analyzing SpaceX with the maps of a world that no longer exists.

12
00:00:41,185 --> 00:00:45,448
The top valuation multiples market window they count.

13
00:00:45,448 --> 00:00:49,711
Like counting the stones of a temple that is burning.

14
00:00:49,711 --> 00:00:51,079
It wasn't an IPO.

15
00:00:51,079 --> 00:00:52,688
It was a referendum.

16
00:00:52,688 --> 00:00:57,514
And the question was written nowhere, but everyone heard it.

17
00:00:57,514 --> 00:01:00,249
In what world do you want to live?

18
00:01:00,249 --> 00:01:01,858
On one side, 1 camp.

19
00:01:01,858 --> 00:01:14,085
That of those who seek the true, who reward those who do, who still laugh. The camp where one builds rockets because the stars are beautiful and we can.

20
00:01:14,085 --> 00:01:19,554
Life that overflows, merit that pays fun is proof that we are alive.

21
00:01:19,554 --> 00:01:22,289
On the other side, the other camp.

22
00:01:22,289 --> 00:01:22,933
Control.

23
00:01:22,933 --> 00:01:23,737
The leash.

24
00:01:23,737 --> 00:01:32,184
The form in triplicate, the camp that doesn't want to kill you, it just wants you to stop doing anything.

25
00:01:32,184 --> 00:01:42,641
Slow death, literally boredom, erected as a system Big Brother, but in a Gray suit, explaining to you that it's for your own good.

26
00:01:42,641 --> 00:01:55,913
For 50 years, this second camp has reigned. It held the pencil, the accounts, the boundaries of the possible. It taught an entire civilization to ask for permission.

27
00:01:55,913 --> 00:01:58,648
That world is dead. Not in theory.

28
00:01:58,648 --> 00:01:59,694
Not tomorrow.

29
00:01:59,694 --> 00:02:00,016
Now.

30
00:02:00,016 --> 00:02:06,934
These people around me who never invest and who want SpaceX, they are not speculators.

31
00:02:06,934 --> 00:02:16,023
They are people who sensed, before even being able to formulate it, which side of the table they wanted to be on.

32
00:02:16,023 --> 00:02:17,873
It's not an investment.

33
00:02:17,873 --> 00:02:18,839
It's a vote.

34
00:02:18,839 --> 00:02:25,113
And the vote says we are handing the keys of the shop back to those who build.

35
00:02:25,113 --> 00:02:29,376
The future does not belong to those who measure risk.

36
00:02:29,376 --> 00:02:31,950
It belongs to those who take it.

37
00:02:31,950 --> 00:02:35,087
I've been saying it from the beginning.

